<ArticleLayout
  title="How to Maintain Leather Upholstery"
  description="How to clean and condition leather sofas and armchairs without damaging the finish, and when to call a professional leather cleaning service."
>
  <p>Leather is a natural material. Without proper care, it dries out, loses flexibility, and can crack over time.</p>

  <h2>Cleaning stage</h2>
  <p>Leather pores collect body oils and fine dirt. Over time this creates a sticky dark film. A pH-balanced cleaner removes buildup while respecting the finish.</p>

  <h2>Conditioning stage</h2>
  <p>After cleaning, conditioning helps restore suppleness and surface protection. This extends leather life and helps reduce future staining.</p>
</ArticleLayout>
